 that ,, so for the time being until my first big project or first job for me ubutu and wsl are just backend engines i need to do my internship am i right on that</div></div><button type="button" aria-controls="_r_90_" aria-expanded="false" class="A_HxFq_toggleControl select-none" data-testid="collapsible-user-message-toggle"><span class="A_HxFq_showMoreLabel">Show more</span><span class="A_HxFq_showLessLabel">Show less</span><div class="A_HxFq_toggleIconWrapper motion-safe:transition-transform motion-safe:duration-150"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" class="A_HxFq_toggleIcon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-16f983c9.svg#ba3792" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></div></button></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex justify-end"><div aria-label="Your message actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto touch:opacity-100 duration-300 group-hover/turn-messages:delay-300 pointer-events-none opacity-0 motion-safe:transition-opacity group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:opacity-100 group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:opacity-100 has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:opacity-100" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface-hover rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy message" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-16f983c9.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface-hover rounded-lg" aria-label="Edit message" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-16f983c9.svg#6d87e1" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button></div></div></div></div><span class="sr-only"><br></span></section></div><div class="" data-turn-id-container="4ae66701-5a77-49ae-8b4d-fb4388719fd9" data-is-intersecting="true"><section class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto R6Vx5W_threadScrollVars scroll-mb-[calc(var(--scroll-root-safe-area-inset-bottom,0px)+var(--thread-response-height))] scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" data-turn-id="4ae66701-5a77-49ae-8b4d-fb4388719fd9" data-turn-id-container="4ae66701-5a77-49ae-8b4d-fb4388719fd9" data-testid="conversation-turn-738" data-turn="assistant"><h4 class="sr-only select-none">ChatGPT said:</h4><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div data-conversation-screenshot-content="" class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="4ae66701-5a77-49ae-8b4d-fb4388719fd9" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="83"><strong data-start="0" data-end="8">Yes.</strong> Your understanding is <strong data-start="31" data-end="55">about 90–95% correct</strong>. Let me refine it slightly.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="1o4cznc" data-start="85" data-end="133">Your understanding (with a small correction)</h3>
<blockquote data-start="135" data-end="246">
<p data-start="137" data-end="246"><strong data-start="137" data-end="246">Ubuntu is used for Linux commands to perform operations on containers because containers are Linux-based.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="248" data-end="258">✅ Correct.</p>
<p data-start="260" data-end="275">More precisely:</p>
<ul data-start="277" data-end="495">
<li data-section-id="136azyj" data-start="277" data-end="328">
<p data-start="279" data-end="328">Docker containers usually run Linux applications.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="wn1k26" data-start="329" data-end="366">
<p data-start="331" data-end="366">Ubuntu is a Linux operating system.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1e3fl1k" data-start="367" data-end="495">
<p data-start="369" data-end="495">If you open Ubuntu, you're inside a real Linux environment where you can use Linux commands (<code data-start="462" data-end="466">ls</code>, <code data-start="468" data-end="472">cd</code>, <code data-start="474" data-end="481">mkdir</code>, <code data-start="483" data-end="487">rm</code>, etc.).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="497" data-end="500">
<blockquote data-start="502" data-end="606">
<p data-start="504" data-end="606"><strong data-start="504" data-end="606">WSL is like Microsoft's provided Linux virtual machine on my Windows laptop that helps Ubuntu run.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="608" data-end="625">✅ Mostly correct.</p>
<p data-start="627" data-end="811">The only refinement is that WSL is <strong data-start="662" data-end="699">not a traditional virtual machine</strong> like VirtualBox or VMware. It's a compatibility layer/subsystem that lets Linux run efficiently inside Windows.</p>
<p data-start="813" data-end="838">A simple mental model is:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="840" data-end="961"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="contents"><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-16f983c9.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼs ͼ16"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Windows</span><br><span>    │</span><br><span>    ▼</span><br><span>WSL (runs Linux)</span><br><span>    │</span><br><span>    ▼</span><br><span>Ubuntu</span><br><span>    │</span><br><span>    ▼</span><br><span>Docker Engine</span><br><span>    │</span><br><span>    ▼</span><br><span>Your Containers</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="963" data-end="1071">For learning purposes, thinking of it as "a lightweight Linux environment inside Windows" is perfectly fine.</p>
<hr data-start="1073" data-end="1076">
<h3 data-section-id="1o0yrac" data-start="1078" data-end="1101">For your internship</h3>
<p data-start="1103" data-end="1111">Exactly.</p>
<p data-start="1113" data-end="1147">Right now your workflow is simply:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1149" data-end="1289"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="contents"><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-16f983c9.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼs ͼ16"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>VS Code</span><br><span>      │</span><br><span>      ▼</span><br><span>Python</span><br><span>      │</span><br><span>      ▼</span><br><span>Docker Desktop</span><br><span>      │</span><br><span>      ▼</span><br><span>WSL (automatic)</span><br><span>      │</span><br><span>      ▼</span><br><span>Ubuntu (automatic)</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1291" data-end="1314">You only interact with:</p>
<ul data-start="1316" data-end="1378">
<li data-section-id="1snl79h" data-start="1316" data-end="1327">
<p data-start="1318" data-end="1327">✅ VS Code</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1e7yb63" data-start="1328" data-end="1346">
<p data-start="1330" data-end="1346">✅ Docker Desktop</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="630p6o" data-start="1347" data-end="1378">
<p data-start="1349" data-end="1378">✅ Command Prompt / PowerShell</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1380" data-end="1438">WSL and Ubuntu are doing their work <strong data-start="1416" data-end="1437">behind the scenes</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="1440" data-end="1443">
<h3 data-section-id="10w1174" data-start="1445" data-end="1476">Later (LegalAI / First Job)</h3>
<p data-start="1478" data-end="1600">When you deploy your LegalAI project to a cloud server like AWS, Azure, or a Linux VM, you'll start using Ubuntu directly.</p>
<p data-start="1602" data-end="1668">For example, you'll log into a Linux server and run commands like:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1670" data-end="1726"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="contents"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="relative h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="select-none sticky z-2 top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-16f983c9.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Bash</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-16f983c9.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼs ͼ16"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>docker compose up </span><span class="ͼ12">-d</span><br><span class="ͼ10">git</span><span> pull</span><br><span>python main.py</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1728" data-end="1832">At that point, Ubuntu becomes a tool <strong data-start="1765" data-end="1785">you actively use</strong>, not just something running in the background.</p>
<hr data-start="1834" data-end="1837">
<h3 data-section-id="nt12ye" data-start="1839" data-end="1860">My advice for you</h3>
<p data-start="1862" data-end="1952">Since you're aiming for <strong data-start="1886" data-end="1910">Cloud + AI + Backend</strong>, don't worry about mastering Linux today.</p>
<p data-start="1954" data-end="1989">Just keep this progression in mind:</p>
<ol data-start="1991" data-end="2185">
<li data-section-id="18gj6ov" data-start="1991" data-end="2008">
<p data-start="1994" data-end="2008">✅ Learn Python</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1s24kls" data-start="2009" data-end="2027">
<p data-start="2012" data-end="2027">✅ Learn FastAPI</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1ecj18v" data-start="2028" data-end="2049">
<p data-start="2031" data-end="2049">✅ Learn PostgreSQL</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1eeq916" data-start="2050" data-end="2067">
<p data-start="2053" data-end="2067">✅ Learn Docker</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1j5nkt1" data-start="2068" data-end="2082">
<p data-start="2071" data-end="2082">✅ Learn Git</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1d124xg" data-start="2083" data-end="2152">
<p data-start="2086" data-end="2152">🔜 Learn basic Linux commands (20–30 commands are enough to start)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="17jlppf" data-start="2153" data-end="2185">
<p data-start="2156" data-end="2185">🔜 Learn AWS/Azure deployment</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="2187" data-end="2375" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">You're already on <strong data-start="2205" data-end="2215">step 4</strong>, which is solid progress. When you eventually deploy LegalAI to the cloud, WSL and Ubuntu will stop feeling like "magic" and start feeling like familiar tools.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start"><div aria-label="Response actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none touch:w-[calc(100%+--spacing(3.5))] -mt-1 w-[calc(100%+--spacing(2.5))] duration-[1.5s] focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto pointer-events-none [mask-image:linear-gradient(to_right,black_33%,transparent_66%)] [mask-size:300%_100%] [mask-position:100%_0%] motion-safe:transition-[mask-position] group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:[mask-position:0_0]" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface-hover rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy response" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-16f983c9.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface-hover rounded-lg" aria-label="Good response" aria-pressed="false" data-testid="good-response-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="